s and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705202,"age":9,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705205,"age":20,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"William Croscomb was born about 1549, in Devon, England. He had at least 4 sons and 2 daughters."},"et":{"about 1549–":"umbes 1549–Surnud","1568–Male":"1568–Surnud","1572–Male":"1572–Surnud","1575–Male":"1575–Surnud","1577–Male":"1577–Surnud","1577–1629":"1577–1629","1580–1581":"1580–1581","1549–Male":"1549–Surnud","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1568":"1568","about 1549":"umbes 1549","1577":"1577","1575":"1575","1572":"1572","1581":"1581","1580":"1580","1629":"1629","1549":"1549","Of Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fi":{"about 1549–":"noin 1549–Kuollut","1568–Male":"1568–Kuollut","1572–Male":"1572–Kuollut","1575–Male":"1575–Kuollut","1577–Male":"1577–Kuollut","1577–1629":"1577–1629","1580–1581":"1580–1581","1549–Male":"1549–Kuollut","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1568":"1568","about 1549":"noin 1549","1577":"1577","1575":"1575","1572":"1572","1581":"1581","1580":"1580","1629":"1629","1549":"1549","Of Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fr":{"about 1549–":"environ 1549–Décédé","1568–Male":"1568–Décédé","1572–Male":"1572–Décédé","1575–Male":"1575–Décédé","1577–Male":"1577–Décédé","1577–1629":"1577–1629","1580–1581":"1580–1581","1549–Male":"1549–Décédé","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1568